# Scheduling & booking (optional)

## Staff logins
- Groomers: https://mobiledog-salon.com/groomer/login (Melanie / Diamond / Jessica)
- Admin: https://mobiledog-salon.com/admin/login

## Environment variables (Vercel production)

Required for persistent appointments on Vercel:
- `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL` — from [Upstash Redis](https://upstash.com) (Vercel marketplace integration)
- `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN`

Session security (recommended in production):
- `SCHEDULING_SESSION_SECRET` — long random string for cookie encryption

Calendar email invites when a customer books (2-hour Outlook calendar events):
- `RESEND_API_KEY` — from [Resend](https://resend.com)
- `BOOKING_EMAIL_FROM` — e.g. `Mobile Dog Salon <bookings@mobiledog-salon.com>` (verified domain)
- `BOOKING_ORGANIZER_EMAIL` — organizer on calendar invites (defaults to bookings@)

Customer booking confirmations (email + optional SMS — simpler than Go High Level):
- Same `RESEND_API_KEY` sends the customer a confirmation email with calendar attachment
- `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID` — from [Twilio Console](https://console.twilio.com) (starts with `AC...`)
- `TWILIO_API_KEY_SID` + `TWILIO_API_KEY_SECRET` — API key credentials (recommended), **or** `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN`
- `TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER` — your Twilio phone number in E.164, e.g. `+17145551234`

SMS is sent only when the customer opts in on the booking form (`smsOptIn`).

Test: `node scripts/test-twilio-connection.mjs`

Twilio inbound SMS webhook (configure in Console → Phone Number → Messaging):
- Webhook URL: `https://mobiledog-salon.com/api/twilio/inbound` (HTTP POST)
- Handles START, STOP, HELP keywords for A2P compliance

Print A2P registration copy: `node scripts/print-a2p-campaign-info.mjs`

### Appointment reminders (24h + 2h before)

When a customer books, **Upstash QStash** schedules two callbacks to send reminders at the right time. A **daily Vercel Cron** (Hobby plan) runs as a backup sweep for anything missed.

- **Email** to every confirmed booking at **24 hours** and **2 hours** before
- **SMS** at the same times when the customer opted in (`smsOptIn`)

Required:
- Same `RESEND_API_KEY` and Twilio vars as confirmations above
- `CRON_SECRET` — Vercel sends `Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>` to `/api/cron/reminders`
- **Upstash QStash** (same Upstash account as Redis):
  - `QSTASH_TOKEN` — from [Upstash Console → QStash](https://console.upstash.com/qstash)
  - `QSTASH_CURRENT_SIGNING_KEY` and `QSTASH_NEXT_SIGNING_KEY` — QStash signing keys
  - `QSTASH_CALLBACK_URL` — `https://mobiledog-salon.com` (production base URL for callbacks)

Manual test:
```bash
node scripts/run-reminders.mjs
# production backup sweep:
SMOKE_BASE_URL=https://mobiledog-salon.com node scripts/run-reminders.mjs
```

Cron backup schedule: daily at 16:00 UTC in `vercel.json`. Per-appointment timing uses QStash.

Optional routing accuracy (not required):
- `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` — Geocoding API for street-level addresses on groomer routes (optional; ZIP fallbacks still work without it).

### Localhost (production appointment data)

Pull env vars from Vercel into `.env.local` (gitignored):

```bash
vercel env pull .env.local --environment=production
```

Then restart the local server (`npm run 67` or `npm run dev`).

Optional password overrides (plain text, per account):
- `SCHEDULING_PASSWORD_MELANIE` — Melanie groomer login
- `SCHEDULING_PASSWORD_DIAMOND` — Diamond groomer login
- `SCHEDULING_PASSWORD_JESSICA` — Jessica groomer login (Chris uses same account)

Jessica trial booking window (customer self-booking):
- `JESSICA_TRIAL_BOOKING_RESTRICTED` — set to `0` or `false` to lift the trial cap (default: restricted)
- `JESSICA_BOOKING_HORIZON_DAYS` — max days ahead customers can book Jessica (default: `7`)

## Client payment portal (Square)

Client portal: https://mobiledog-salon.com/client/login  
Staff portal: sign in at groomer/admin login → **Payments** tab

### Get Square credentials

1. Sign in at [Square Developer Dashboard](https://developer.squareup.com/apps)
2. Open your application (or create one)
3. Copy **Application ID** → `SQUARE_APPLICATION_ID`
4. Under Credentials, create/copy **Access token** → `SQUARE_ACCESS_TOKEN`
5. In Square Dashboard → Locations, copy your location ID → `SQUARE_LOCATION_ID`
6. Set `SQUARE_ENVIRONMENT` to `sandbox` for testing or `production` for live charges

Required for live card processing:
- `SQUARE_ACCESS_TOKEN` — Square API access token
- `SQUARE_APPLICATION_ID` — Square application ID (Web Payments SDK)
- `SQUARE_LOCATION_ID` — Square business location ID
- `SQUARE_ENVIRONMENT` — `sandbox` or `production`

Optional:
- `CLIENT_SESSION_SECRET` — separate cookie encryption for client accounts

Client accounts stored in `data/clients.json` (or Upstash Redis when configured).

### Licky AI chat (client portal)

Off by default. To enable:
- `LICKY_ENABLED=1` — server (chat API)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_LICKY_ENABLED=1` — show the chat widget (set both on Vercel, then redeploy)

Required when Licky is enabled:
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` — from [OpenAI API keys](https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)

Optional:
- `OPENAI_MODEL` — defaults to `gpt-4o-mini` (fast, cost-effective for support chat)

**Production:** Add `OPENAI_API_KEY` in Vercel → Project → Environment Variables → Production.

Or run (with your key):
```bash
node scripts/connect-licky.mjs sk-your-openai-key
npm run test-licky
```

**Production (required):** Install [Upstash for Redis](https://vercel.com/marketplace/upstash) on your Vercel project.
The integration sets `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL` / `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN` (or `KV_REST_API_URL` / `KV_REST_API_TOKEN`).
Without Redis, groomer saves fail on production and schedules reset on deploy.

Availability **history** (for admin restore) is stored in the same Redis database.

## Go High Level (confirmation emails + reminders)

When a customer books, the site syncs to Go High Level so you can send **automatic confirmation emails and appointment reminders**.

### 1. API credentials (Vercel env vars)

1. In GHL → **Settings** → **Business Profile** → copy **Location ID** → `GHL_LOCATION_ID`
2. GHL → **Settings** → **Integrations** → **Private Integrations** → Create key with scopes:
   - `contacts.write`, `contacts.readonly`
   - `calendars.write`, `calendars.readonly`
   - `calendars/events.write`
   - `workflows.write` (if using workflow enrollment)
3. `GHL_API_KEY` — the private integration token

Test locally: `node scripts/test-ghl-connection.mjs` (lists your GHL calendars)

### 2. Calendar IDs (triggers GHL appointment emails)

Each booking creates a **GHL calendar appointment** with `toNotify: true`, which fires GHL's built-in confirmation + reminder system.

1. GHL → **Calendars** → open Melanie's calendar → copy calendar ID
2. Repeat for Diamond (or use one shared calendar)

```
GHL_CALENDAR_ID_MELANIE=...
GHL_CALENDAR_ID_DIAMOND=...
GHL_CALENDAR_ID_JESSICA=...
# or a single shared calendar:
GHL_CALENDAR_ID=...
```

Optional: `GHL_USER_ID_MELANIE`, `GHL_USER_ID_DIAMOND` to assign appointments to staff users.

### 3. Confirmation + reminder workflow (recommended)

Create a workflow in GHL → **Automation**:

**Option A — Customer Booked Appointment trigger** (if using calendar API above)
1. Trigger: **Customer Booked Appointment** → filter to your MDS calendar(s)
2. Action: **Send Email** — booking confirmation template
3. Action: **Wait** → until 24 hours before appointment
4. Action: **Send Email** or **Send SMS** — reminder
5. Action: **Wait** → until 2 hours before appointment
6. Action: **Send SMS** — day-of reminder (filter: tag `sms-opt-in`)

**Option B — Inbound Webhook trigger** (works without calendar IDs)
1. Trigger: **Inbound Webhook** → copy URL → `GHL_WEBHOOK_URL`
2. Map webhook fields (`firstName`, `email`, `appointmentDate`, `appointmentTime`, `petName`, `groomer`, etc.)
3. Same email + wait + reminder actions as above

**Option C — Add to existing workflow via API**
1. Copy workflow ID from GHL workflow URL → `GHL_BOOKING_WORKFLOW_ID`
2. Each booking enrolls the contact into that workflow automatically

### 4. Custom contact fields (optional, for email merge tags)

Create these custom fields in GHL → **Settings** → **Custom Fields** (Contact):

`pet_name`, `pet_breed`, `pet_size`, `service`, `service_price`, `groomer`, `appointment_date`, `appointment_time`, `appointment_address`, `booking_id`, `booking_notes`

The booking API upserts these on every contact automatically.

### 5. Add all vars to Vercel

Project → **mobile-dog-salon** → Settings → Environment Variables → Production:

```
GHL_API_KEY=
GHL_LOCATION_ID=
GHL_CALENDAR_ID_MELANIE=
GHL_CALENDAR_ID_DIAMOND=
GHL_BOOKING_WORKFLOW_ID=   (optional)
GHL_WEBHOOK_URL=           (optional)
```

## Local development
Data is stored in `data/scheduling.json` and `data/clients.json` without Redis.
Keep `data/scheduling.json` availability empty in git — groomers set hours via the dashboard.

**Match production availability locally:** Add the same Upstash/Vercel KV vars to `.env.local` so local dev reads the live Redis database:

```
KV_REST_API_URL=
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
```

Run `vercel env pull .env.local --environment=production` from the project root, or copy these from Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables. Without Redis locally, the booking calendar will be empty even though production has groomer hours.
